- TAKE GUN -", "I have my gun with me, they should be afraid of me…", "Anyway… what is taking him so long? ", "Did he get lost or something? It’s just following a road, how hard could it be?", "A few miles from the car you spot something in the middle of the road. You draw your gun and get closer to examine.", "Hey, I’m armed, don’t try anything funny!", "No answer.", "You approach even closer.", "You can see what it is now!", "You begin to panic, your world is turned upside down.", "A thousand thoughts run through your mind.", "Did a bear do this? But he said there aren’t any bears around here. ", "What the fuck happened!?", "You suddenly realize you’re in danger as well.", "You feel a shiver down your spine. The air feels too heavy to breathe.", "You realize you are not alone. Something is slowly coming at you.", "You feel its presence getting closer.", "Petrified you hold your gun in front of you ready to fire at anything that moves.", "I have to act fast!", "DYNAMIC", "DYNAMIC", "DYNAMIC", "- DONT TAKE GUN + GO OUTSIDE THE CAR -", "You decide to go outside, telling yourself there’s nothing to fear here. That it’s just a stupid road in the middle of the night.", "Choosing not to take your gun is a decision. It's easy to get frightened out here and accidentally shoot something.", "The most potentially dangerous things in this area are hungry raccoons and deer.", "Anyway… what is taking him so long? Did he get lost or something? It’s just following a road, how hard could it be?", "A few miles from the car you spot something in the middle of the road.", "You reluctantly get closer to examine.", "As you pick up your cell phone to light the way ahead, you notice a bright yellow color further down the road. ", "Immediately the image of the taxi driver’s jacket comes into your mind.", "It can’t be him, it must be my mind playing tricks again.", "Get a hold of yourself, Vesper.  ", "Step by step as you approach, the image down the road becomes clearer.", "You shout, preoccupied.", "Hey, are you okay? What happened?", "You approach even closer. You can see what it is now.", "You begin to panic, your world is turned upside down. A thousand thoughts run through your mind. ", "Did a bear do this? But there aren’t any bears around here. What happened? ", "You suddenly realize you’re in danger as well. Petrified you start to run back to the cab.", "Running desperately you hear your name spoken in the shadows. ", "Oh, Vesper. Running away is futile.", "I must be going crazy, this can’t be real.", "It’s just a flat tire, in the middle of a god-forsaken road that leads nowhere!", "You’re not real!", "Oh… but I am.", "The figure is in front of you. A tall dark-haired man, with piercing black eyes and fangs. ", "Fangs?", "You’re stuck in place, terrified. There’s nowhere to run. ", "The man slowly but steadily approaches you.", "A vivid memory flashes before your eyes, as you realize the mistake you’ve made.", "He was there, the entire time. Amongst everyone, inconspicuous.", "Before you have time to say something he jumps on you and bites your neck.", "You lose consciousness from the shock.", "- KIDNAPPED DAY 1 -", "You wake up tied to a chair, with your hands behind your back. ", "Feeling very weak and nauseated, you want to throw up, but you’re not strong enough to vomit.", "Where am I? ", "You look at your surroundings, they don’t look familiar. You’re in a large room with only one window.", "Strangely enough, there’s a big lockpad on it.", "The floor is a dirty mess, with blood splattered all over. You’ve come to realize the mess you’ve gotten yourself into.", "How much time has passed?", "You can see from the outside some sunlight passing through the dark curtains. It looks like a few hours have passed.", "You hear loud moans coming from the next room.", "Wait, moaning? Hello… is anybody there?", "No answer. The moaning intensifies.", "Someone seems to be having a good time…", "You feel terrible but at the same time, you feel like blushing.", "It’s like you were sucked into another dimension, a dark, gritty, sexual dimension.", "After the events last night you don’t know what’s real anymore.", "The door slowly opens, it seems like they didn’t bother to close the door all the way down.", "Your vision is still blurred so you can’t make out who exactly they are, but you can see a girl with long blond hair and a tall muscular man with long dark hair.", "You avert your eyes.", "After a while the moaning stops, the door opens and the couple approaches you. ", "Who are you?! What are going to do with me?", "...", "Who is she?", "That’s the woman I talked to you about. ", "The one who’s been asking about me all over town?", "Exactly.", "Hello? I’m right here.", "Shut up, livestock.", "Easy… she’s scared.", "The woman looks deeply into your eyes; you can see compassion in them.", "What is your name, honey?", "It’s Vesper… ", "I presume you know who I am?", "Your skin is much paler than in the pictures, and your hair is much longer, but I’m pretty sure you’re Helena Bergman.", "Indeed.  (She smiles at you) - Change Portrait", "The man on the other hand looks at you with deep hatred in his eyes.", "Now, why have you been asking about me? Wasn't it clear I didn’t want to be found?", "I’m a reporter, my job is to investigate.", "I see. And that’s the only reason?", "She stares at you like she’s gazing at your soul.", "……………….", "You can’t seem to lie to her.", "No.", "I…", "Enough talk, I’m getting tired of all this mumbling.", "Oh, honey, please, let me have this. How long have we been holed up in this place all by ourselves?", "It's been months since I’ve talked to anybody else, and those other girls you brought could barely speak.", "Fine… you’re too soft, Helena.", "The man sneers and returns to the bedroom, slamming the door behind him.", "You feel less threatened with him gone.", "Now, beautiful, what were you saying?", " I… it all started as a job. But, the closer I got to you, the more I investigated your life, it was like an obsession.", "I felt like I knew what you were going through.", " I went to the same places you did, talked to the same people… I even went to your house and talked to your mom.", "When she was not looking I lay down on your bed and thought about how it felt to be you. I never had a room of my own.", "That’s cute…You even talked to my mom, huh… I doubt she was of any help.", "I’m sorry. ", "Don’t be… she was always like that. She only had eyes for my father, ", "I was the product of her misfortune; falling in love with a beast.", "But I guess history has a way of repeating itself.", "You notice her hands shaking.", "There is still time, you don’t have to do this. ", "Now that I have found you, we could run away, I’ll get us to a safe place far away from him.", "Oh, honey. What do you think is happening here?", "He kidnapped you, forced you into doing terrible things. All these girls…", "Do I look like I’ve been kidnapped?", "Ahn… no…", "I’m sure you were brainwashed somehow, that man, he can do things that aren’t natural. He’s not human.", "That’s correct, we are not human. I haven’t been human for a long time now.", "You pull back, confused.", "Are you scared of me now?", "Your voice quivers.", "No… ", "You should be.", "I’m not scared of you. All these girls… he was the one who killed them all, not you.", "For an investigative reporter, you sure are naive.", "Don't you think it's too much of a coincidence the murders started to happen only after my disappearance?", "Put the facts together, you already have all the answers.", "No! I don’t believe it. I can’t…", "Denying the truth doesn’t make it less painful.", "But why? You’re not like this, Helena.", "I wasn’t like this. You don’t understand, you think you do, but you don’t.", "She begins to shake harder.", "He didn't force me into anything. I asked him to make me like this. So we could be together, forever.", "But I didn’t know, the hunger would consume me. He said it's different for everyone.", "It drives my every thought, even as we speak, I feel like ripping your throat apart and draining your blood dry.", "What you see now is a hollow shell of what I once was.", "I… I’m so sorry, Helena, you didn’t deserve this. (PORTRAIT your eyes begins to fill with tears)", "Are you… pitying me? You should be afraid for yourself.", "Helena gets closer to your throat her fangs protracted, she bites you leaving you in a trance.", "As she lets go you fall sideways, (SCENE : Blood dripping down your neck. Helena ashamed of herself picks you up and starts to cry.)", "--- KIDNAPPED DAY 2 ---", "You wake up a few hours later, feeling weaker than the day before. You don’t know how much time you have left, but it doesn’t feel like much.", "You know now what were the girls’ fate, and what will be your fate if you don't find a way to escape. ", "You try to escape, but how?", "DYNAMIC", "DYNAMIC", "-- Back to EscapeOptions - ", "You can’t even hold your eyes open, your mouth is dry. You have a massive headache and your body hurts all over.", "You finally give up...", "Hours pass, with you drifting in and out of sleep.", "By night the man comes over. You can see by his expression that he’s livid.", "What did you say to her!?", "You try to muster all your strength to answer.", "Nothing, we just talked… ", "I should have just killed you the moment I laid my eyes on you.", "Don’t forget you are here for the sole purpose of feeding us.", "Terrified, tears start streaming down your cheeks.", "Maybe I should just put you out of your misery? So, you stop putting ideas on Helena’s head.", "The man bites you in the arm and starts choking you.", "Helena enters the room.", "What are you doing to her!?", "…", "Stop it now, please…", "He lets go of you.", "You feel like a rag doll, with no strength left whatsoever.", "Helena embraces you. ", "Tsc. Fine, let’s see how much longer you can hold without drinking her dry.", "The man leaves the room.", "Vesper… I’m sorry. I don’t want to be like this.", "You gaze into her eyes with the innocence of a helpless child. Even now, you can’t feel hatred towards her.", "Vesper, I don't think I can hold it any longer. I can feel your heart beating, slower every time. ", "I want to consume you, to devour your entire being and make you mine.", "But I know that's wrong, that's what my dad did to me all these years.", "It wasn’t just the physical abuse, but treating me like I was an object only meant to satisfy his animalistic desires.", " I can’t keep on like this…", "Vesper, please, save me. Let’s escape together, tomorrow, okay?", "I mean it, I won’t be able to stop myself. I want you. I want to feel you, I want to drown myself in your blood. I want to kill you.", "This is going to be our only chance.", "Will you trust me? ", "- REFUSE -", "So be it… I promise to make it fast.", "Let’s become one, my beautiful Vesper.", "Helena sinks her teeth deep into your neck, causing your blood to gush everywhere. She moans with pleasure as she drinks from you until the very last drop.", "- DEATH FOR REFUSAL -
- ACCEPT - ", "I'm glad you trust me. I promise to take care of you.", "Tomorrow we’ll escape during the day. We’re on the 5th floor, there are no stairs nor elevators leading here. The only way in or out is through that window.", "Unfortunately, you’re too weak to escape by yourself, and I can’t control myself around you while you’re still human.", "The only way for us to do this is for you to share my curse.", "When I do this your heart is going to stop beating. You’ll be like us, undead.", "Well, not exactly like us… the transformation is different for each of us.", "Your actions will shape what you’ll be in the future.", "I pray that you don't turn out as bloodthirsty and sex driven as I am.", "But one can only hope.", "Helena slits her wrist and pours her blood into your mouth.", "You can’t resist, you don’t want to, even after all that has transpired you are still obsessed with this creature.", "You drink her blood and immediately start to feel a sense of foreboding.", "Losing all sense of self, your heart beats faster than ever. Gazing at Helena’s big blue eyes is a mixture of looking at the sky and the bottom of the ocean.", "Sinking into the abyss, you start convulsing, you’re not just dying, you’re transforming into something else. A state between life and death, an aberration.", "And finally...", "Your heart stops.", "When you wake up you’ve lost all track of time. it feels like days have passed. ", "All you can remember is Helena’s voice telling you to wait for her. ", "You feel terrible, like a truck ran over you. You’re cold all over and you realize you're not breathing.", "You start to panic.", "You inhale and exhale many times trying to calm down. It seems your body remembers how to breathe, it just doesn't need to.", "How am I alive? What’s happening?", "Your vision is blurry and you’re not strong enough to keep your eyes open.", "What’s going on? Is it day or night? Where’s Helena?", "You hear sounds coming from the window. Someone is messing with the lockpad.", "Hey… who….", "Sheesh… be quiet, honey. I’ll come to you in a sec.", "You hear a loud clank.", "Her footsteps get closer to you until they stop. You can feel her right in front of you.", "She bends down and whispers: ", "I’ve managed to secure us a car. He’s suspicious enough already. ", "I told him you’re dead. In a sense you are…", "Am I? ", "Half-dead, undead, the living dead…", "Vampire…", "…", "From now on things will be rough, but that was the only way to get us out of here. During the night he would’ve followed us anywhere.", "I need you to trust me again. I’m doing this for both our sakes.", "I do.", "I’m glad to hear that.", "Alright, here’s the situation. You’re a vampire now, but you haven’t even fed once, your body is still fighting to remain human.", "So, a quick exposure to the sun shouldn’t kill you, at least for now.", "“Shouldn’t” ?", "In theory, yes. From what I was told sunlight becomes more harmful to us the more we've fed.", "But how are you going outside?", "I'll help you down first, then you bring the car aaround. I couldn't park it close enough or he would've noticed.", "…", "I know it's not the perfect plan, but staying here is certain death, at least this way you got a chance.", "Alright.", "From now on you’ll have to deal with that hunger daily. It will accompany you for the rest of your life.", "I’ll explain more once you’re safe. Quick, let’s go before he wakes up.", "Helena unfastens your bindings.", "You try to stand up but stumble and fall.", "Oh no, you’re weaker than I thought you would be.", "We don’t have enough time to change plans now.", "Helena bends down and pulls you to her back.", "Hold on tight. Don’t let go, no matter what, okay?", "You latch on to her as hard as you can. You smell her hair, it comforts you.", "That’s it. I’ll take care of you.", "She starts moving closer to the window.", "The door opens abruptly.", "What do you think you’re doing, Helena?", "Helena turns to face him.", "I can’t keep doing this, this is not right.", "I’ve done awful things these past months, but talking to Vesper made me remember what I once was.", "Helena moves closer to the window, and grabs the thick black curtain.", "Please, Helena, don’t do this. Why are you doing this to us? She’s just livestock, a plaything.", "You’re wrong. She’s much more, she’s hope. She’s the one who’s going to pull me out from this darkness.", "I love you, Clive. I always will. But I refuse to be like my mother. Forgive me.", "Helena pulls the curtain and jumps down the window.", "You feel a terrible discomfort when the sun touches your skin, a burning sensation invading your every being.", "Nooo!!!", "You land like a rock on the floor, if you were human there’s no chance you would have survived the fall.", "Helena clutching the curtain in her hands swiftly covers you as best as she can.", "Don’t worry, he can’t follow us here. We have to be quick, I don’t have much longer.", "You can hear her skin sizzling. She’s trying to hide it, but from her voice, you can notice she’s in excruciating pain.", "Helena, please, stop. I don’t want you to… ", "As you get closer to the car, you can feel Helena getting weaker by the moment.", "We can’t go back now, baby.", "The car is right in front of you, doors unlocked, key in the ignition.", "This is my farewell gift to you. Get in the car and drive away, live for as long as you can. Forgive me.", "She drops to her knees and gives you one last smile.", "Goodbye, my sweet Ves….", "You hear her last words as she turns to dust.", "Helena...", "You get in the car.", "There's only one thing you can do right now.", "-- END OF PROLOGUE --", "You drive away as fast as you can. Your head is in turmoil. You can’t think straight.", "You were always searching for adventure, for the unknown. And now that you have found it, you can’t believe it actually happened.", "Are you still you? ", "Is this a curse or a gift?", "Will you turn out like Helena, unable to contain the hunger? Or like Clive, with an ultimate disdain for people around you? ", "I guess only time will tell… ", "For now, I need to go home and think about my next steps.", "Helena, I’ll never forget you… ", "-- END OF KIDNAPPED --
