ld try and talk to people about it... discreetly.", "How much would it cost me anyway? I spent too much following Helena's trail, I can barely afford the rent.", "I was planning to sell her story once I'd found her, once I'd solved the mistery.", "It's not like I can do that anymore...", "Congratulations, Vesper. You got more than what you wished for.", "You throw your notes about Helena in the trash can and set them on fire.", "Oh well, new life I guess... or should I say...new death? ", "You start to feel dizzy with hunger, and all the unanswered questions. ", "Just thinking about it won’t do me any good, I should prepare. ", "What’s the best course of action?", "-- END OF ACT 1 ---
